# Prometheus `basic_auth.username_file` for scraping the ADMIN-gated /actuator/prometheus (M5).
#
# Copy this file to `metrics_user` (no extension) in this directory and replace the placeholder
# below with the RAW admin USERNAME - i.e. the half BEFORE the first ':' of
# THEBULLPEN_ADMIN_BASIC_AUTH - with NO trailing newline. Easiest: run
# infra/prometheus/mk-metrics-secrets.sh, which writes BOTH metrics_user + metrics_pw from
# THEBULLPEN_ADMIN_BASIC_AUTH. Manual:
#
#   printf '%s' "${THEBULLPEN_ADMIN_BASIC_AUTH%%:*}" > metrics_user
#
# Kept in a FILE (not inline as basic_auth.username in prometheus.yml) so ANY admin username works
# with no repo edit and nothing credentialed lives in the committed config. The real metrics_user is
# gitignored; only this `.example` is committed. (Comment lines are fine here because Prometheus
# never reads `.example`, only the real metrics_user, which must contain ONLY the username string.)
REPLACE_WITH_RAW_ADMIN_USERNAME
